Hangman Game
This is a simple command-line Hangman game written in Python. The game randomly selects a word, and the player must guess the word letter by letter. The player has a limited number of attempts to guess the word correctly before the game ends.

Features
Randomly selects a word from a predefined list.
Allows the player to guess the word letter by letter.
Displays the hangman figure as incorrect guesses are made.
Tracks the number of remaining attempts.
Provides feedback on the player's guesses.
Allows the player to play multiple rounds.

Game Flow
Welcome Message: The game begins with a welcome message explaining the rules.
Word Selection: The game randomly selects a word from a predefined list.
Guessing: The player is prompted to guess one letter at a time.
If the guessed letter is correct, it will be revealed in the word.
If the guessed letter is incorrect, a part of the hangman figure will be drawn.
Winning: The player wins if they guess all the letters of the word correctly before running out of attempts.
Losing: The player loses if they run out of attempts before guessing the word.
Play Again: After the game ends, the player is given the option to play again.
